  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA159-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu talaiviyiṉ (G1+2: talaivi) āṟṟāmaiyum ulakiyaluṅ kūṟi varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how marriage was asked for, talking about HER lack of strength and the nature of the world.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA159">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            maṇituṇin taṉṉa māyirum parappi</l>
<l>            ṉuravuttirai keḻīiya pūmali peruntuṟai</l>
<l>            nilavukkuvit taṉṉa mōṭṭumaṇa liṭikaraik</l>
<l>            kōṭutuṇarn taṉṉa kurukoḻuk keṇṇi</l>
<l>            yellai kaḻippiṉa māyiṉ mella </l>
<l>            vaḷicīttu varitta puṉṉai muṉṟiṟ</l>
<l>            koḻumī ṉārkaic ceḻunakarc celīiya</l>
<l>            veḻuveṉi ṉavaḷu mollāḷ yāmu</l>
<l>            moḻiyeṉa valla māyiṉam yāmat</l>
<l>            tuṭaitirai yoliyiṟ ṟuñcu malikaṭaṟ </l>
<l>            cilkuṭip pākkaṅ kalleṉa</l>
<l>            valkuva tākanī yayarnta tērē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent2">When we spent the daytime,</l>
<l rend="indent3">counting flocks of herons clustered like conches</l>
<l rend="indent">on the crumbling shore with sand in peaks heaped like moonlight<note place="foot">For this comparison cf. KT 123.2.</note></l>
<l rend="indent">on the big ghat abounding in flowers embraced by the strong waves</l>
<l rend="indent">of the big dark extension clear like a sapphire,</l>
<l rend="indent2">when [I] said:</l>
<l rend="indent2">“up! let [us] go [back] to the mansion abundant in eating rich fish</l>
<l rend="indent2">[and] a front yard with Puṉṉai trees softly swept [and] drawn</l>
<l rend="indent4">by the wind”,</l>
<l rend="indent">she did not consent and we</l>
<l rend="indent">ended up not speaking a word [to each other]<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">moḻi eṉa allam āyiṉam</term>: presumably <term xml:lang="ta">eṉa</term> has to be taken here as a real infinitive, and then the phrase might be literally: "we became those who are not such as to speak a word".</note>.</l>
<l>Let the chariot you ride stay openly(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kalleṉa</term> might either refer to the noise made by the chariot and thus imply the idea of not hiding the fact of its coming, or to the noisy gossip subsequently arising in the village.</note></l>
<l rend="indent2">in the village with small homes by the great sea,</l>
<l rend="indent2">where they sleep with the sound of the breaking waves at midnight.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
